Cash advance apps like Varo, Payactiv, MoneyLion, Dave, EarnIn, and Empower are another option today. They typically offer advances of $1,000 or less and must be repaid within a short time frame, such as 30 days or when you receive your next paycheck.

The interest rates these apps charge also tend to be high, over 100% in some cases when expressed as an annual percentage rate (APR). Plus, on top of that you may have to pay other fees.3

